			<h1 itemprop="name headline  "
								>How to make perfect Cornish pasties</h1>
		
					<p itemprop="description" id="stand-first"
				 class="stand-first-alone"                    data-component="Article:standfirst_cta"			>Traditional recipes call for shortcrust pastry encasing beef, potatoes, swede and onion – but do you prefer cheese and onion, chicken and vegetable or even a clanger or a bridie?<br /><br />• <a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/lifeandstyle/gallery/2013/mar/04/world-pasty-championships-in-pictures">The World Pasty Championships – in pictures</a></p>
		
		
